children.name: This page consists of 3 basic typography components: Heading, Text, and Link. Each component frame has information about its variants, specifications, and states (if applicable). The specifications contains information about typography tokens that are being used at different breakpoints. All components are added as a text style so that it can be easily used across components for consistency.
children.characters:
This page consists of 3 basic typography components: Heading, Text, and Link. 

Each component frame has information about its variants, specifications, and states (if applicable). The specifications contains information about typography tokens that are being used at different breakpoints. 

All components are added as a text style so that it can be easily used across components for consistency.

children.name: To see all text styles, ensure that objects on the page aren’t selected. The list of styles can be found in the Design tab in the panel on the right hand side. To view or edit the styles, you can select the edit button to see text style properties which should link back to typography token values.

children.name: The typography tokens on this page are used as reference in the design system which can be found in storybook here: https://radius-ds.netlify.com/?path=/docs/foundations-typography-tokens--page On this page, you will find typography tokens that are used throughout the Radius Design System. We have defined a basic typography scale and styles that are most commonly used. With these tokens, it can be used to construct typography components which are added as a text style in Figma.

On this page, you will find typography tokens that are used throughout the Radius Design System. We have defined a basic typography scale and styles that are most commonly used. With these tokens, it can be used to construct typography components which are added as a text style in Figma.

children.name: Note: If you update tokens on this page, ensure that your changes are reflected in the component library, work with your development team to update token values. Also, be sure to update text styles that use the tokens from this page as well.

children.name: This page consists of colour tokens in a light and dark theme and are used as reference in the design system which can be found in storybook here: https://radius-ds.netlify.com/?path=/docs/foundations-color-tokens--page Colours are organized into 4 categories: Brand, UI, Background, and Text. All colour tokens are added as a colour style so that it may be easily accessed. Colour token names are displayed beneath each colour swatch.

children.name: The spacing components on this page are used as reference for spacing tokens in the design system which can be found in storybook here: https://radius-ds.netlify.com/?path=/docs/foundations-other-tokens--space The spacing tokens are Intended to be used for margin, padding, grid gaps, positioning and other layout-related CSS properties. This is an intentional constraint that makes it difficult to add one-off or in-between sizes that could lead to unwanted and rippling affects to layout. See component pages to see how it is used.
